        <section id="collection-steven-kurutz" class="steven-kurutz-collection collection" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/CollectionPage">
        <header class="collection-header">
        <div class="collection-meta">
            <div class="collection-meta-header">
    <div class="supported-by nocontent robots-nocontent hidden">
    <span class="ad-label">Supported by</span>
    <div id="SupportedBy" class="supported-by-ad ad"></div>
</div>    <h3 class="kicker">
        <span class="kicker-label">
            <a href=""></a>
        </span>
            </h3>
</div><!-- close collection-meta-header -->
            <div class="collection-meta-group">

                                <div class="collection-image">
                    <img src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/09/25/multimedia/author-steven-kurutz/author-steven-kurutz-thumbLarge.png" />
                </div>
                
                <div class="collection-headings">

    <div class="collection-heading-group">

                                 
            <h1 class="collection-heading" itemprop="name">
                Steven Kurutz            </h1>
                                        <div class="follow-button-placeholder" style="" data-collection-id="byline.steven-kurutz"></div>
                    
            </div><!-- close collection-heading-group -->

    
    
            <h2 class="collection-subheading" itemprop="about">Steven Kurutz is a reporter in the Style department. He has written about Boyd's of Philadelphia, the last great men's clothing store; the Sock Queen of Alabama; David Bowie's invisible life in New York; a filmmaker who documents dead malls; and Matthew McConaughey's unique brand of zen, among many other stories.                        <a class="user-action">More<i class="icon caret-icon"></i></a>
                    </h2>
    
    
</div><!-- close collection-headings -->

            </div>
        </div>
            </header>
            <div class="collection-description">
        <p>Steven Kurutz is a reporter in the Style department. He has written about Boyd's of Philadelphia,<a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2018/03/29/style/the-last-great-clothing-store-boyds.html"> the last great men's clothing store</a>; the <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2016/03/31/fashion/sock-business-alabama.html">Sock Queen of Alabama</a>; David Bowie's <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2016/01/17/fashion/david-bowie-invisible-new-yorker.html">invisible life</a> in New York; a filmmaker who documents <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2016/12/08/fashion/mens-style/the-tao-of-matthew-mcconaughey.html">dead malls</a>; and Matthew McConaughey's <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2016/12/08/fashion/mens-style/the-tao-of-matthew-mcconaughey.html">unique brand of zen</a>, among many other stories.</p>
<p>Mr. Kurutz started his career at The Times writing for the City section and was also a reporter for the Home section. Before joining The Times in 2011, he was a culture reporter for The Wall Street Journal and a staff writer at Details.</p>    </div>
    
    

    
